  "prompt": "Why is HBO drama The Newsroom being canceled after the third season?",
  "response": "\"The Newsroom,\" created by Aaron Sorkin, was canceled after its third season primarily due to declining viewership and mixed critical reception. While the show had a passionate fanbase and received accolades for its writing and performances, particularly from star Jeff Daniels, the ratings did not meet HBO's expectations. Additionally, Sorkin expressed that he had told the story he wanted to tell, and he felt it was time to conclude the series. The third season was designed to wrap up the storylines and provide a sense of closure for the characters and the overarching narrative.",
